The course consists of regular classes, where wer learn to use different video equipment and software. It is followed by theoretical part which is parallel with daily tasks that we will watch and feedback in the next class. The course ends with a larger scale video production process that will have a public screening as an exam in the end of the semester.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to learn the main principles of a professional camera and editing as a tool for a specialist to create different mediums. While creating different mediums, we will thoroughly learn the preproduction process for creating film or video (idea, script, preparation, shooting, post-production).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has finished the course -is familiar with the principles of using a camera and its technical aspects - can use editing software for editing personal footage - has experienced the preproduction process for atleast two video formats
